==English==

{{rank|heaven|v.|difficult|801|top|tone|silent|takes}}

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[summit]] or [[crest]]''

===Noun===
'''top''' (''plural:'' '''[[tops]]''')

#That part of an object furthest away in the opposite direction from that in which an unsupported object would fall.<!-- This is gibberish. What does it mean? -->
#The part seen, or intended to be seen, nearest the edge of the visual field normally occupied by the uppermost visible objects.<!-- More gibberish. -->
#:''Headings appear at the tops of pages.''
#A [[lid]], [[cap]] or [[cover]] of a container.
#A [[garment]] worn to cover the [[torso]].
#A child’s [[spin]]ning [[toy]].
#{{baseball}} The first half of an inning, the visitor’s half of an inning
#(''sexual slang'') A [[dominant]] partner in a [[BDSM]] relationship or roleplay.
#(''gay sexual slang'') A gay man who likes to [[penetrate]] in [[anal sex]] rather than be penetrated.

